@startuml
' @id(DOM-FONT-DATABASE)
' @id(DOM-OCL-VIEW)
' @id(DOM-PUML-SOURCE-VIEW)
' @desc(DOM-FONT-DATABASE, "The font database the SVG rasterizer depends on; populated once with system fonts before the first parse/render.")
' @desc(DOM-OCL-VIEW, "Viewer state for a selected .ocl constraint file: sub_mode (Source = raw OCL text, Diagram = synthesized constraints SVG) and the loaded diagram page.")
' @desc(DOM-PUML-SOURCE-VIEW, "Viewer state backing the central-panel Source toggle for ordinary model files: the path whose text is loaded and the cached raw .puml source. When the top-level View is Source the viewer paints this text read-only instead of the rendered SVG; reading the file requires no renderer.")
' Objective-side viewer domain: the font database the SVG rasterizer
' depends on, the OCL-view state, and the PlantUML Source-view state that
' backs the central-panel Diagram | Source | Diff toggle.
title Viewer domain — font database + OCL view + PlantUML source (objective)

enum OclSubMode {
  Source
  Diagram
}

class SvgRasterizer {
  + parse(bytes) : Tree
  + render(tree, scale) : Pixmap
}

class FontDatabase {
  + fontCount : int
  + defaultFamily : String
  + loadSystemFonts() : void
}

class OclView {
  + subMode : OclSubMode
  + sourceText : String
  + page : Option<DiagramPage>
  + renderedSvg(oclPath) : Path
}

class SourceView {
  + loaded : Option<String>
  + source : String
}

SvgRasterizer "1" o-- "1" FontDatabase : resolves <text> via >
OclView --> OclSubMode

note bottom of FontDatabase
  Populated once with the host's system fonts
  before the first parse/render. Constrained by
  OCL-FONTDB-POPULATED.
end note

note bottom of OclView
  Source paints sourceText (read-only); Diagram
  paints the synthesized constraints SVG on the
  shared canvas. subMode is exactly one of
  {Source, Diagram}; Diagram requires the
  rendered SVG to exist, else a placeholder
  (OCL-OCL-VIEW-SUBMODE, OCL-OCL-DIAGRAM-NEEDS-RENDER).
end note

note bottom of SourceView
  Backs the central-panel "Source" toggle (between
  "Diagram" and "Diff") for ordinary model files.
  `loaded` is the path whose text is in `source`, read
  once per selection from disk. When the top-level View
  is Source the viewer paints `source` read-only and
  scrollable, never a rendered artifact — the Source
  view is always self-sufficient (OCL-PUML-SOURCE-NO-RENDER).
end note
@enduml
